The paper deals with subgraph sampling and its applications in dynamic graph streams, distributed systems, and parameterized problems. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories such as data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG) which often deals with sampling techniques. However, since the paper primarily focuses on graph algorithms and their analysis, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant but to a lesser extent.
